import java.math.BigInteger;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
	private static BigInteger gcd(BigInteger a,BigInteger b) {
		if(b.equals(BigInteger.ZERO)) return a;
		return gcd(b,a.remainder(b));
	}
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner kb = new Scanner(System.in);
		while(true) {
			BigInteger a = new BigInteger(kb.next());
			BigInteger b = new BigInteger(kb.next());
			if(a.equals(b)) break;
			while(true) {
				if(a.equals(BigInteger.ONE)) {
					System.out.println(b);
					break;
				}
				BigInteger q = (b.divide(a)).add(BigInteger.ONE);
				System.out.print(q + " ");
				BigInteger num = (a.multiply(q)).subtract(b);
				BigInteger den = b.multiply(q);
				BigInteger g = gcd(num,den);
				a = num.divide(g);
				b = den.divide(g);
			}
		}
		kb.close();
	}
}
